comments: As Adams (MEM) and Poeltl (SAS) engage for a position in the post, marginal contact occurs.
Vassell (SAS) moves alongside Morant's (MEM) path and marginal body contact occurs as he contests the driving shot attempt.
As Adams (MEM) secures the loose ball, marginal contact occurs from Poeltl (SAS).
Poeltl (SAS) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Bane's (MEM) driving shot attempt.
Brooks (MEM) engages with Johnson (SAS) during the initial pick, and the contact is marginal.
Brooks (MEM) initiates contact with Johnson (SAS) by impeding him and affecting his FOM off-ball.
Marginal contact occurs as Morant (MEM) is firming up in Jones' (SAS) path during the screen.
As Jones (SAS) and Morant (MEM) engage during the screen, Jones flails his arm, causing contact to occur with Morant's head.
Brooks (MEM) is the last to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Poeltl (SAS) and Adams (MEM) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Adams (MEM) establishes himself in Jones' (SAS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Jones (SAS) legally contests Brooks' (MEM) jump shot attempt.
Brooks' (MEM) shot does not hit the rim before the shot clock expires.
McDermott (SAS) extends his arm toward Brooks (MEM) and marginal contact occurs as he moves over the screen.
Brooks (MEM) contests the shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Johnson's (SAS) arm after the release.
Adams (MEM) immediately slides his hand off of Poeltl's (SAS) side and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Poeltl (SAS) contests the driving shot attempt and marginal body contact occurs with Morant (MEM) after the release.
Poeltl (SAS) dislodges the ball prior to incidental contact occurring with Konchar (MEM) on the rebound.
Bane (MEM) makes clean contact with the ball before incidental body contact occurs with Poeltl (SAS) on the loose ball, and a jump ball is correctly called.
Poeltl (SAS) establishes himself in Brooks' (MEM) path and his legs remain within the frame of his body as contact occurs, which he does not deliver.
Konchar (MEM) takes less than 5 seconds to release the inbounds pass.
A timeout is signaled for and correctly awarded prior to the inbound pass.
Adams (MEM) establishes himself in Jones' (SAS) path and absorbs the contact on the pick.
Adams (MEM) deflects the ball out of bounds.
Bane (MEM) makes marginal contact with Johnson's (SAS) arm in transition.
Johnson (SAS) initiates contact with Bane's (MEM) arm that dislodges the ball.
Johnson (SAS) makes marginal contact with Bane (MEM) after Bane releases the pass.
Johnson (SAS) makes marginal contact with Brooks' (MEM) body after Brooks releases the pass.
Jones (SAS) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Morant's (MEM) driving shot attempt.
Konchar (MEM) makes marginal contact with Sochan's (SAS) arm after his gather during the driving shot attempt.

The game clock stops at 00:19.7 for five seconds at the start of a SAS transition, and restarts following the made basket and inbound. At the next immediate stoppage at 14.3, referees conference and determine that the clock needed to be reset to 9.3 seconds.
Jones (SAS) makes marginal contact as he pressures Bane (MEM) near the baseline.
Vassell (SAS) attempts to commit a take foul on Morant (MEM), but does not make contact.
Vassell (SAS) commits a take foul on Morant (MEM).
Bane (MEM) places a marginal arm on Vassell (SAS) as they briefly engage and separate off-ball.
Brooks (MEM) legally contests Vassell's (SAS) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
